<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p></p><div class="quoteright" style="width:300px;"><div class="lazy_load_img_box" style="padding-top:140.29%"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/sv_poster1.png" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/sv_poster1.png" width="350" height="491"></div></div><p></p><div class="indent"><em>Have you seen a cultivation world where people used horses and carriages all day? Have you seen a cultivation world where after achieving inedia, people still needed to eat and sleep? Have you seen a cultivation world where the author occasionally mixed up even the Foundation Establishment and Nascent Soul stages?</em><p></p></div><div class="indent"><em>Every single person, when in front of the protagonist, would act like his aura of "awesomeness" had devoured their intelligence. Especially Luo Binghe's master, that Shen Qingqiu, basically an idiot among idiots, scum among scum! His only purpose was to dig his own grave, and when he didn't manage to finish, get killed by the protagonist.</em><p></p></div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><div class="indent"><em>Then why did Shen Yuan read this book, and even read to the very end?</em><p></p><div class="indent"> &mdash; <strong>Chapter 1</strong></div></div><p><em>Ren Zha Fan Pai Zi Jiu Xi Tong</em> (&#20154;&#28195;&#21453;&#27966;&#33258;&#25937;&#31995;&#32479;) or "The Scum Villain's Self-Saving System" is a danmei <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Xianxia" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Xianxia">Xianxia</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WebNovel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WebNovel">Web Novel</a> written by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/MoXiangTongXiu" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/MoXiangTongXiu">Mo Xiang Tong Xiu</a>.</p><p>The story goes like this: after his death, Shen Yuan finds himself in the world of a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HaremGenre" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HaremGenre">stallion novel</a> that he likened to trash shortly before he died. As per the genre, one would expect him to reincarnate as the protagonist, right?</p><p>Wrong. Instead, he transmigrated into the body of Shen Qingqiu, the titular "scum villain" who, in the novel's canon, eventually gets killed by the <em>actual</em> protagonist Luo Binghe for being a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SadistTeacher" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SadistTeacher">Sadist Teacher</a>. Determined to avoid the same fate, Shen Yuan uses his knowledge of the novel's plot and tropes to endear himself to the characters (especially to the protagonist), which would ensure that he keeps his life.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><p>Unfortunately for him, he's accompanied by a video game-like "system" that monitors and grades his actions, keeping him from taking too many liberties with how his character acts and how the story progresses. And if he ignores its warnings, the consequences will be deadly. Thus his foray into the world of cultivation begins...</p><p>An English translation of the novel is available at <a class="urllink" href="http://bcnovels.com/the-scum-villains-self-saving-system/">BC Novels<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>. A <a class="urllink" href="https://faelicy.tumblr.com/post/185035206852/scum-villain-table-of-contents">re-translation of the novel<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> by faelicy is available and currently ongoing.</p><p>An <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimatedAdaptation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimatedAdaptation">Animated Adaptation</a> of the novel, titled <em>Chuan Shu Zi Jiu Zhi Nan</em> (&#31359;&#20070;&#33258;&#25937;&#25351;&#21335;) or "Using the Self-Saving Guide Book" with the official English title of "Scumbag System," was announced; and started airing on September 10, 2020. A <em>manhua</em> was also released on August 28, 2019; although after the first three chapters were released, the <em>manhua</em> was suddenly taken down and put on a hiatus for undisclosed reasons.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><hr><h2> This work contains the following tropes:</h2><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccidentalPervert" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccidentalPervert">Accidental Pervert</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Shen Yuan accidentally grabs a certain part of Luo Binghe's body when they are hiding in a coffin inside of the Holy Masoleum together.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AbilityRequiredToProceed" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AbilityRequiredToProceed">Ability Required to Proceed</a>: The System is a constant source of this particular sort of annoyance for Shen Yuan.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AbductionIsLove" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AbductionIsLove">Abduction Is Love</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Luo Binghe abducts Shen Yuan a few times throughout the course of the novel, though Shen Qingqiu isn't exactly unwilling to go.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActionGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActionGirl">Action Girl</a>: Every named female character in the novel.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AcquittedTooLate" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AcquittedTooLate">Acquitted Too Late</a>: Shen Yuan gets accused of several crimes performed by the original, and is framed for others. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> It's only after his death via self destruction when he's acquitted for said crimes off-page.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActOfTrueLove" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActOfTrueLove">Act of True Love</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Shen Yuan and a crazed Luo Binghe have some very physically painful sex in the end, finally convincing Luo Binghe that Shen Yuan truly does want him in his life.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationalAttractiveness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationalAttractiveness">Adaptational Attractiveness</a>: Shen Yuan in the newly released trailer for the upcoming donghua has been unanimously considered to be a pretty boy by the fandom.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AffectionateNickname" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AffectionateNickname">Affectionate Nickname</a>: Shizun, by Luo Binghe.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AffectionateParody" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AffectionateParody">Affectionate Parody</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AGirlInEveryPort" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AGirlInEveryPort">A Girl in Every Port</a>: Basically the entire plot of the original <em>Proud Immortal Demon Way</em>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllThereInTheManual" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllThereInTheManual">All There in the Manual</a>: The novel has several extras which tell stories about side characters, missing scenes, and post-novel events. Many of those extras are necessary to understanding side characters' backstories (Shen Jiu, Yue Qingyuan, etc.), and were originally released only in the printed novels.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimalMotifs" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimalMotifs">Animal Motifs</a>: Luo Binghe is often compared to a fluffy sheep or dog.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AntagonistInMourning" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AntagonistInMourning">Antagonist in Mourning</a>: How the cultivation world views Luo Binghe after <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Shen Yuan died via self-destruction</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorityEqualsAsskicking" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorityEqualsAsskicking">Authority Equals Asskicking</a>: the Peak Lords of Cang Qiong sect are quite powerful, to the point where all of the gathered sects freeze in fear when Yue Qingyuan lets an inch of his sword out of its scabbard.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadSamaritan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadSamaritan">Bad Samaritan</a>: The Huan Hua palace master's intentions in accepting Luo Binghe into his sect post-abyss aren't exactly noble...</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BenchedHero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BenchedHero">Benched Hero</a>: Luo Binghe is in the Abyss for three years before he returns to the scene.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BetaCouple" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BetaCouple">Beta Couple</a>: Shang Qinghua and Mobei Jun. Their relationship is explored in more detail in the extras.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BellisariosMaxim" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BellisariosMaxim">Bellisario's Maxim</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse">In-Universe</a>. A very very large amount of suspension of disbelief is needed to even get through a single chapter of the original <em>Proud Immortal Demon Way</em>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BileFascination" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BileFascination">Bile Fascination</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse">In-Universe</a>. This describes <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CausticCritic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CausticCritic">Shen Yuan's</a> relationship with the original novel, with a side of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GuiltyPleasure" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GuiltyPleasure">Guilty Pleasure</a> (he did read the whole thing, after all).</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreakingTheFourthWall" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreakingTheFourthWall">Breaking the Fourth Wall</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButThouMust" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButThouMust">But Thou Must!</a>: Despite all his attempts to establish a positive relationship with Luo Binghe, Shen Yuan is notified by the System that the scene where he pushes Luo Binghe into the Endless Abyss is absolutely unavoidable.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Chickification" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Chickification">Chickification</a>: One of Shen Yuan's frustrations with the original novel. How do so many women in the original novel who are trained to use flying freaking swords and battle magic constantly needing to be saved?</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClearMyName" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClearMyName">Clear My Name</a>: Shen Yuan is accused of several crimes and is imprisoned in the Huan Hua Palace's Water Prison, and can only sit there and wait for his trial in the hopes that his fellow Peak Lords can gather enough evidence to free him, but realizes it might be a lost cause.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ColdBloodedTorture" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ColdBloodedTorture">Cold-Blooded Torture</a>: What happened to the original Shen Qingqiu (Shen Jiu) after Luo Binghe got his hands on him (includes: having all of his limbs ripped off, his eye ripped out and tongue as well, and in the meantime - as a cherry on top - Luo Binghe killed the only person Shen Jiu actually cared about.) It definitely wasn't pretty. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Shen Yuan himself gets to experience what Shen Jiu went through during the punishment protocol sequence - having his arm and leg ripped off by the original Luo Binghe was definitely terrifying</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ComicBooksAreReal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ComicBooksAreReal">Comic Books Are Real</a>: Shen Yuan thought that the characters and story of <em>Proud Immortal Demon Way</em> was just part of regular trashy web novel. After <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrappedInAnotherWorld" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrappedInAnotherWorld">he is transmigrated after his death</a>, he finds out the story is its own dimension. The canonical events of the novel where <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForWantOfANail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForWantOfANail">Shen Yuan didn't transmigrate into Shen Qingqiu</a> exists as its own dimension and timeline.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CouldHaveAvoidedThisPlot" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CouldHaveAvoidedThisPlot">"Could Have Avoided This!" Plot</a>: Shen Yuan realizes towards the end that he made several mistakes throughout the course of the story, and that he could have found another way around pushing Luo Binghe into the Abyss by simply talking with him about it, which would have saved both of them a lot of emotional pain.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CruelAndUnusualDeath" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CruelAndUnusualDeath">Cruel and Unusual Death</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeconstructorFleet" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeconstructorFleet">Deconstructor Fleet</a>: Of the harem and the isekai/transmigration genre.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoesNotLikeMen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoesNotLikeMen">Does Not Like Men</a>: Xian Shu peak, lead by Qi Qingqi, only accepts female disciples.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoorstopBaby" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoorstopBaby">Doorstop Baby</a>: Infant Luo Binghe was adopted by the old washerwoman who found him floating down the Luo River.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EasilyThwartedAlienInvasion" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EasilyThwartedAlienInvasion">Easily Thwarted Alien Invasion</a>: The demons attempting to attack Cang Qiong sect, led by Sha Hualing, are easily defeated and leave the sect resentful over their humiliation.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvenTheGuysWantHim" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvenTheGuysWantHim">Even the Guys Want Him</a>: Shen Qingqiu. A running fandom joke is that Shen Yuan transmigrated into an awful harem novel and accidentally snagged a harem of his own, namely: Luo Binghe, Yue Qingyuan, Liu Qingge, and Zhuzhi-lang.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnemyMine" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnemyMine">Enemy Mine</a>: Luo Binghe teams up with the righteous cultivation sects to defeat Tianlang-Jun.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FaceOfAnAngelMindOfADemon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FaceOfAnAngelMindOfADemon">Face of an Angel, Mind of a Demon</a>: Both the original Shen Qingqiu and original Luo Binghe.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FakingTheDead" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FakingTheDead">Faking the Dead</a>: Shen Qingqiu did this as a plan to escape death by Luo Binghe's hands. Unfortunately, needless to say, the consequences were not good.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FemaleGaze" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FemaleGaze">Female Gaze</a>: <em>The Resentment of Chunshan</em> is an in-universe fanfiction depicting Luo Binghe's and Shen Yuan's relationship, written by none other than Liu Mingyan.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FirstEpisodeResurrection" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FirstEpisodeResurrection">First Episode Resurrection</a>: First chapter begins with fervent anti-fan Shen Yuan cursing the poorly written web novel <em>Proud Immortal Demon Way</em> with his last breath. He then wakes up as a character of said novel, tasked by the System to improve the events of the story.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FirstLawOfResurrection" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FirstLawOfResurrection">First Law of Resurrection</a>: Shen Yuan is the worst offender of this trope, managing to die and get somehow revived no less than <em>three times</em> throughout the course of the novel.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FixFic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FixFic">Fix Fic</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse">In-Universe</a>. The transmigrators intended to live and changed events so it&#146;s better in their favor. In the process, they allowed character development and the romance plots falls to them instead of a lady.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Foreshadowing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Foreshadowing">Foreshadowing</a>: When the Little Palace Mistress asks Luo Binghe where her father is, Luo Binghe casually replies that he disappeared and no one has found any sign of him. Shen Yuan mentally notes that anyone who gives that answer is usually responsible for the person going missing. Fifteen chapters or so chapters later, Shen Yuan is proven to be correct: the Old Palace Master was mutilated and kept imprisoned in the Holy Mausoleum.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForWantOfANail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForWantOfANail">For Want of a Nail</a>: Due to Shen Qingqiu's attempts to avert his doom, he tried to support Luo Binghe, unexpectedly leading to the protagonist falling for the original scum villain. The transmigrators realized this when they finally see where Luo Binghe's true affections go to.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GenreShift" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GenreShift">Genre Shift</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse">In-Universe</a>: After a while, the transmigrators realized this when they finally saw Luo Binghe's affections for his Shizun and his lack of interest for women or a harem. Amusingly, the original novel was supposed to be a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Yaoi" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Yaoi">Yaoi</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoneHorriblyRight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoneHorriblyRight">Gone Horribly Right</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GravityIsAHarshMistress" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GravityIsAHarshMistress">Gravity Is a Harsh Mistress</a>: Shang Qinghua: HE (Mobei-jun) CAN'T FLY!</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HaremGenre" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HaremGenre">Harem Genre</a>: The original novel, but emphatically not this one.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IHaveYouNowMyPretty" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IHaveYouNowMyPretty">I Have You Now, My Pretty</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InSpiteOfANail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InSpiteOfANail">In Spite of a Nail</a>: While Shen Yuan's actions drastically alter the plot, someone still gets turned into a human stick. Except that instead of Shen Yuan, it's <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> the Old Palace Master</span> who suffers this fate instead.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Isekai" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Isekai">Isekai</a>: Or as referred to in China, a transmigration novel.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LawOfOneHundred" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LawOfOneHundred">Law of 100</a>: The Jade Guanyin can reduce Luo Binghe's anger points by 3000.<ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> <strong>Would you like to initiate the Self-Saving System?</strong></span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LighterAndSofter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LighterAndSofter">Lighter and Softer</a>: In the donghua, they have to censor. The fate for the original Shen Qingqiu was turned to living in a pickled jar for the rest of his life while the death for Shen Yuan was changed to choking to death.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LongTitle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LongTitle">Long Title</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoopholeAbuse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoopholeAbuse">Loophole Abuse</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InnocenceLost" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InnocenceLost">Innocence Lost</a>: Luo Binghe after being pushed into the Abyss.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MediaTransmigration" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MediaTransmigration">Media Transmigration</a>: Anti-fan Shen Yuan dies from food poisoning after intensely ranting about the terrible end of the web novel he loved to hate-read. He then awakes as a character in said novel... as its <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StarterVillain" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StarterVillain">Starter Villain</a> Peak Lord Shen Qingqiu who dies as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndIMustScream" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndIMustScream">a human stick</a> at the hands of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WishFulfillment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WishFulfillment">Wish Fulfillment</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainProtagonist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainProtagonist">Villain Protagonist</a> Luo Binghe. The plot revolves around Shen Yuan's attempts to avoid this fate by endearing himself to young and innocent Luo Binghe and the resulting consequences.<ul><li> Later it's revealed the author also reincarnated after accidentally electrocuting himself as minor character Shang Qinghua.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MenAreTheExpendableGender" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MenAreTheExpendableGender">Men Are the Expendable Gender</a>: In the original <em>Proud Immortal Demon Way</em>, any male character that could be a possibile threat due to their looks or abilities always manages to get killed off.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MirrorMatch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MirrorMatch">Mirror Match</a>: This happens in one of the extras where the original Luo Binghe crosses over into Shen Yuan's version of <em>Proud Immortal Demon Way</em> and clashes with that version of Luo Binghe.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MiseryPoker" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MiseryPoker">Misery Poker</a>: After Shen Yuan realizes that <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Shang Qinghua is actually &#12298;Airplane Shooting Towards the Sky&#12299;</span>, both of them get into a brief argument about who's having it worse in their transmigrating adventures.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ObliviousToLove" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ObliviousToLove">Oblivious to Love</a>: Shen Qingqiu is the only person in the cast who hasn't noticed that Luo Binghe is in love with him.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OfficialCouple" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OfficialCouple">Official Couple</a>:<ul><li> Shen Yuan and Luo Binghe.</li><li> The author confirmed that Shang Qinghua and Mobei Jun are also an item.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OutOfCharacterAlert" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OutOfCharacterAlert">Out-of-Character Alert</a>: This was one of the first problems Shen Yuan had to overcome by winning enough points by completing certain plot flags. Luckily, it doesn't take long in the story for the restriction to be removed.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Padding" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Padding">Padding</a>: Shen Yuan is of the opinion that the Holy Mausoleum subplot felt like suck in the original novel since it went on for at least a hundred chapters just to explain in vivid detail how Luo Binghe was able to bypass every single death trap in the place. In the revised canon, all the traps are taken care of in two (in-universe) chapters, and Shen Yuan even receives points for "skipping through filler".</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PerceptionFilter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PerceptionFilter">Perception Filter</a>: It's strongly implied that the other characters can't see or hear whenever Shen Yuan is interacting with the System. Otherwise, someone might have eventually asked him why he's acting strangely, why he's talking to thin air, and what he's talking about. It's similar to how a character would suddenly switch weapons or costumes or even behavior in video games because the player paused the menu to change the configurations.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PoorCommunicationKills" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PoorCommunicationKills">Poor Communication Kills</a>: Had Shen Bingqiu and Luo Binghe talk it out, lots of misunderstandings would have been avoided. The latter firmly believed his Shizun hates him and knew he does deserve his ire but never thought to talk it out. The former, while having some details correct, is still stuck on the protagonist be the original and not knowing how to talk, only lash out and be in denial.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PsychicDreamsForEveryone" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PsychicDreamsForEveryone">Psychic Dreams for Everyone</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RealityEnsues" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RealityEnsues">Reality Ensues</a>:<ul><li> As <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Shang Qinghua</span> points out, genuine literary masterpieces are often ignored by the masses in favor of literature that are cheaply written and heavily cliched. While he wants to write genuinely good novels, he still needs the money to make ends meet, hence he turned <em>Proud Immortal Demon Way</em> from the former to the latter.</li><li> In the <em>Return to Childhood</em> extra, Luo Binghe is stuck in his six-year old form as a result of a <em>qi</em> deviation. Even then, he wants to <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> have sex with Shen Yuan</span>... which is impossible, since he's not tall, fit, or strong</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedOniBlueOni" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedOniBlueOni">Red Oni, Blue Oni</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReincarnateInAnotherWorld" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReincarnateInAnotherWorld">Reincarnate in Another World</a>: Shen Yuan dies from food poisoning and wakes up in the body of Shen Qingqiu, the scum villain of <em>Proud Immortal Demon Way</em>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RescueArc" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RescueArc">Rescue Arc</a>: The Holy Mausoleum arc.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SadistTeacher" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SadistTeacher">Sadist Teacher</a>: The original Shen Qingqiu.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Satire" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Satire">Satire</a>: The novel pokes fun at itself for using and subverting <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Yaoi" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Yaoi">Yaoi</a> conventions such as Shen Yuan being at the very least five years older than Luo Binghe while in the body of a much older guy. It also deconstructs the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HaremGenre" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HaremGenre">Harem Genre</a> by having the female characters that aren't connected to the protagonist in a romantic sense.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SceneryPorn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SceneryPorn">Scenery Porn</a>: There are times when the <em>donghua</em> gets to show some rather vivid, even if mildly simplistic, backgrounds.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StartOfDarkness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StartOfDarkness">Start of Darkness</a>: For original Luo Binghe it was from the beginning he became the apprentice of Shen Jiu/Shen Qingqiu, and cemented after being thrown into the Endless Abyss, but for new Luo Binghe, because he was under Shen Yuan/Shen Qingqiu, the start was after the mandatory push into the Endless Abyss, as Shen Yuan really had no other choice.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StatusQuoIsGod" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StatusQuoIsGod">Status Quo Is God</a>: It doesn't matter that Shen Yuan-as-Shen Qingqiu immediately ceased his abuse of Luo Binghe and made him his beloved disciple. It doesn't matter that he became a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoolTeacher" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoolTeacher">Cool Teacher</a> for all of Qing Jing Peak. Shen Yuan must throw Luo Binghe into the Abyss.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuicidalSadisticChoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuicidalSadisticChoice">Suicidal Sadistic Choice</a>: If Shen Yuan doesn&#146;t ensure that Luo Binghe takes the fall into the Endless Abyss and kick off Luo Binghe&#146;s <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StartOfDarkness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StartOfDarkness">Start of Darkness</a>, the resulting loss of System points will kill Shen Yuan. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Years later, Shen Yuan wonders if he could have gotten the same results by asking Luo Binghe to go into the Endless Abyss instead of pushing him in as an act of betrayal.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TeacherStudentRomance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TeacherStudentRomance">Teacher/Student Romance</a>: Shen Yuan (as Shen Qingqiu) and Luo Binghe.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheyWastedAPerfectlyGoodPlot" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheyWastedAPerfectlyGoodPlot">They Wasted a Perfectly Good Plot</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse">In-Universe</a>; this is how Shen Yuan feels about how &#12298;Airplane Shooting Towards the Sky&#12299; handled the story of <em>Proud Immortal Demon Way</em>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrappedInTVLand" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrappedInTVLand">Trapped in TV Land</a>: Shen Yuan, an anti-fan of trashy <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WishFulfillment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WishFulfillment">Wish Fulfillment</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HaremGenre" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HaremGenre">Harem Genre</a> web novel <em>Proud Immortal Demon Way</em> ends up transmigrated into said series after he dies. He is trapped in the role of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SadistTeacher" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SadistTeacher">Sadist Teacher</a> Shen Qingqiu for <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheHero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheHero">The Hero</a> Luo Binghe's backstory. His very presence begins to drastically <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForWantOfANail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForWantOfANail">alter the course of the story.</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnreliableNarrator" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnreliableNarrator">Unreliable Narrator</a>: Shen Qingqiu who missed the protagonist&#146;s true affections and others. He thought the story was set in stone in spite of him helping people grow.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnusualEuphemism" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnusualEuphemism">Unusual Euphemism</a>: "Sky Pillar" for... you know.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VitriolicBestBuds" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VitriolicBestBuds">Vitriolic Best Buds</a>: Shen Yuan and Shang Qinghua have this relationship. Well, sort of; their "friendship" is very complicated.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeWantOurJerkBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeWantOurJerkBack">We Want Our Jerk Back</a>: Averted. After Shen Yuan transmigrates into Shen Qinqui, the other Peak Lords wonder if he's become possessed due to changes in his behavior. However, they decline to pursue the issue because Shen Yuan is <em>so</em> much nicer (and easier to get along with) than the original Shen Qinqui.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhamLine" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhamLine">Wham Line</a>: Chapter 28 reveals that Shen Yuan is actually the <em>second</em> person to transmigrate into the world of Proud Immortal Demon Way. What's even more surprising is <em>who's</em> the first.<div class="indent"> <strong>Shen Yuan</strong>: <em>(to <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Shang Qinghua</span>)</em> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> &#12298;Airplane Shooting Towards the Sky&#12299;</span>? <br><span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> <strong>Shang Qinghua</strong></span>: You... how do you know this ID of mine?</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhoWritesThisCrap" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhoWritesThisCrap">Who Writes This Crap?!</a>: Shen Yuan's reaction to <em>Proud Immortal Demon Way</em> in a nutshell, though it's less of "<em>who</em> writes this crap" and more of "<em>why</em> did the author write this crap".</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WithGreatPowerComesGreatInsanity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WithGreatPowerComesGreatInsanity">With Great Power Comes Great Insanity</a>: Luo Binghe's sword, Xin Mo, is known to devour the minds of its users. This greatly contributes to Luo Binghe's already severe insecurities towards his relationship with Shen Yuan.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WrongGenreSavvy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WrongGenreSavvy">Wrong Genre Savvy</a>: To be fair to Shen Qingqiu, he is in a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HaremGenre" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HaremGenre">stallion</a> novel and has in no way of knowing his actions would change it to a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Yaoi" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Yaoi">Yaoi</a>. There is also a dissonance here as well as the novel the readers are reading is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Yaoi" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Yaoi">Yaoi</a> but in-universe, the original novel was supposed to be a stallion.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Xianxia" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Xianxia">Xianxia</a>: <em>Proud Immortal Demon Way</em> is set in a world where there are cultivators who train to ascend to immortality. However, Shen Yuan also observes that the author also added some supernatural elements that aren't common in the <em>xianxia</em> genre, and the plot in Shen Yuan's canon is mostly character-driven.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YoureNotMyFather" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YoureNotMyFather">You're Not My Father</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Luo Binghe publically refuses to recognize either Su Xiyan or Tianlang-Jun towards the end of the novel, saying that his only parent is the old washerwoman who raised him in his childhood.</span></li></ul><hr>
</div>
